STATE of New Jersey, Plaintiff,
v.
Soliman YOUSSEF, Defendant-Appellant. M-902 September Term 2017
079941 Supreme Court of New Jersey. March 23, 2018

ORDER

This matter having been duly presented to the Court on defendant's appeal as of right from the judgment of the Superior Court, Appellate Division in A-005079-15; and the Court having determined that the matter does not raise a substantial constitutional question under Rule 2:2-1(a)(1) and the applicable case law;

It is ORDERED that the appeal is dismissed on the Court's own motion.
